1. What is RxJS?
RxJS (Reactive Extensions for JavaScript) is a library for reactive programming using Observables to 
handle:
    Asynchronous operations
    Event streams
    HTTP requests
    Use input events
    WebSocket streams
In Angular, RxJS is heavily used in:
    HttpClient
    Router
    Forms
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. what is Observable? How to create? Realtime Usecase?
An Observable is a stream of data over time. It can emit values, errors, or a completion signal. 
Observables are lazy, meaning they don't start emitting values until there is a subscriber.
Key Points:
Lazy (executes only on subscribe)
Can emit multiple values
Can complete or error
Supports cancellation (unsubscribe)

 // Create observabale
    const myObser$ = new Observable((value) => {
      value.next("this basic observable creation demo");
    });

    myObser$.subscribe(message => {
      //debugger;
      console.log("myObser$", message);
    })

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3️⃣ Observable vs Promise
| Feature           | Observable                          | Promise                             |
|-------------------|-------------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| Emission          | Can emit multiple values over time  | Emits a single value or error       |
| Lazy              | Yes                                 | No (eager)                          |
| Cancellation      | Yes (unsubscribe)                   | No                                  |  
| Operators         | Rich set of operators for transformation | No built-in operators, but can chain with .then() callback |
| Error Handling    | Can emit errors as part of the stream | Errors are handled through .catch() |  

Angular prefers Observables because they support streams & cancellation.
