5. What is Subject?

A Subject is both:
Observable
Observer
It can emit values and be subscribed to. Subjects are useful for multicasting (sharing a single execution path among multiple subscribers) 
and for creating hot observables (observables that emit values regardless of subscriptions).

import { Subject } from 'rxjs';
const subject = new Subject();
subject.subscribe(v => console.log(v));
subject.next(100);

6. Types of Subjects (Very Important)
1. Subject
No initial value
Does not replay previous value

2. BehaviorSubject
Requires initial value
Emits last value to new subscribers

const bs = new BehaviorSubject(0);
bs.subscribe(v => console.log("Subscriber 1:", v)); // Logs: Subscriber 1: 0
bs.next(1); // Logs: Subscriber 1: 1
bs.subscribe(v => console.log("Subscriber 2:", v)); // Logs: Subscriber 2

3. ReplaySubject
Replays previous values
Can configure buffer size

4. AsyncSubject
Emits only last value on completion

